      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 6.04,
      "end": 11.14,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.88,
      "end": 15.76,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Assah, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.46,
      "end": 20.86,
      "text": "Aseps fables, the mice, and the weasels.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 21.88,
      "end": 27.7,
      "text": "There was a war between the mice and the weasels, in which the mice always got the",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 27.7,
      "end": 31.7,
      "text": "worst of it, numbers of them being killed and eaten by the weasels.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 32.54,
      "end": 36.94,
      "text": "So they called a council of war, in which an old mouse got up and said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 37.58,
      "end": 42.22,
      "text": "\"'It's no wonder we are always beaten, for we have no generals to plan our battles",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 42.22,
      "end": 45.24,
      "text": "and direct our movements in the field.'\"",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 45.24,
      "end": 51.54,
      "text": "Acting on his advice, they chose the biggest mice to be their leaders, and these, in order",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 51.54,
      "end": 57.02,
      "text": "to be distinguished from the rank and file, provided themselves with helmets bearing large",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 57.02,
      "end": 58.2,
      "text": "plumes of straw.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 58.88,
      "end": 62.68,
      "text": "They then let out the mice to battle, confident of victory.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 63.68,
      "end": 68.84,
      "text": "But they were defeated, as usual, and were soon scampering as fast as they could to their",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 68.84,
      "end": 69.08,
      "text": "holes.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 69.86,
      "end": 75.74,
      "text": "All made their way to safety without difficulty except the leaders, who were so hampered by",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 75.74,
      "end": 80.9,
      "text": "the badges of their rank that they could not get into their holes and felt easy victims",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 80.9,
      "end": 82.2,
      "text": "to their pursuers.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 83.7,
      "end": 85.82,
      "text": "Greatness carries its own penalties.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
